 SENATE President Ahmad Lawan, has distributed food palliatives to thousands of residents in Damaturu and the six local government areas in Yobe North Senatorial District of Yobe State. The local governments are: Bade, Nguru, Jakusko, Yusufari, Karasuwa, and Machina, respectively. The gesture by Senator Lawan, according to a statement by his Special Assistant (Press), Ezrel Tabiowo, in Abuja, yesterday, was to give succour to members of his constituency, who are affected by the lockdown policy following the spread of the COVID-19 disease. Besides the food items, also donated to the people are infrared thermometers, chemicals for disinfection, sprayers, hand sanitisers, face masks, hand gloves and boots. 